                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; a few lines on
                           the incipit page of the Text, alternating with black lines; incipit of
                           each section of the text; abbreviations; names of Hebrew letters in Ps.
                           118 (e.g., fol. 28va); some other words, e.g., wa-kāʿǝba (e.g., fol.
                           4vb), halle luya (e.g., fols. 5rb, 5vab), wa-tǝbǝl (e.g., fols. 48vb,
                           49rab), qǝdmä wangel (e.g., fols. 14ra, 15va), wa-ʾǝmzǝ (e.g., fols.
                           16vb, 20va), ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 17ra, 18ra), mǝʿrāf (e.g., fol. 18rb);
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals; elements of the punctuation signs and text
                           dividers.</seg>
                     </handNote>
